{
  "text": "Loss function Given a sequence of 2D joint locations as input, our network predicts a sequence of 3D joint locations relative to the root node (central hip). We predict each 3D pose in the camera coordinate space instead of predicting them in an arbitrary global frame as suggested by Martinez et al. [CITATION_1] .",
